  "takeaway": [
    "The gate's non-circular interaction-recovery lift SURVIVES on the polar/directional classes: within the sub-2A (correct) subset, accepted poses recover more crystal H-bonds and pi-stacking than rejected poses by +0.07-0.08 (CI excludes 0 for both AF3 and Chai) -- LARGER than the untyped-4.5A gap (+0.03-0.04) and larger than the hydrophobic-only gap (+0.04-0.05).",
    "So the lift is NOT just hydrophobic-contact count / ligand-in-pocket: the chemically meaningful directional interactions are exactly where the gate separates accepted from rejected poses most. Salt bridges (rare; median 2/pose, present in ~half of systems) also show a positive gap, significant for Chai (+0.041, CI excludes 0) and marginal for AF3 (+0.034, CI touches 0).",
    "Verdict: the non-circular quality claim is chemically credible under typed interaction fingerprints -- it holds per interaction class, most strongly for the polar/directional interactions a medicinal chemist reads for SAR, not only for hydrophobic bulk."
